      "dimensions": "H 9 cm x D 7,2 cm",
      "description": "Gin no Kizuna is a yunomi restored through gintsugi (銀継ぎ), repaired with real silver. Once heavily damaged, it required multiple careful stages of reconstruction, making it the most complex restoration I have completed so far. Each fracture was patiently rejoined, transforming breakage into quiet strength. Now perfectly functional, fully food safe, and ready to hold tea again, it carries both its history and its renewal within the silver lines.",
